			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I'm sad to announce that the Textual Confirmation Code Has Been Cracked by Spammers.  <img src="images/smiles/icon_evil.gif" alt="Evil or Very Mad" border="0" /> 
<br />

<br />
I have the code installed on 3 of my forums and starting a couple of weeks I started to get a lot of spam.  At first I thought it was being done manually, but with the amount I'm getting now I suspect they found away around the code with their BOTS.  I also changed all my Textual Confirmation questions and that didn't help.  The Code has been Cracked!
<br />

<br />
Hope you guys can fix it!</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
